a|year=2008|publisher=University of Pennsylvania Press|location=Philadelphia|isbn=978-0-8122-4052-8|ref=none}}\n* {{citation |last=Barrett |first=Timothy Hugh |title=The Woman Who Discovered Printing |year=2008 |publisher=[[Yale University Press]]|location=Great Britain |isbn=978-0-300-12728-7 |ref=none}}\n* {{citation|last=Cotterell|first=Arthur|title=The Imperial Capitals of China: An Inside View of the Celestial Empire|year=2007|publisher=Pimlico|location=London|isbn=978-1-84595-009-5|ref=none}}\n* {{citation|last=de la Vaissi\u00e8re|first=E.|title=Sogdian Traders. A History|year=2005|publisher=Brill|location=Leiden|isbn=978-90-04-14252-7|ref=none}}\n* {{citation|last=Schafer|first=Edward H.|title=The Vermilion Bird: T'ang Images of the South|year=1967|publisher=University of California Press |location=Berkeley and Los Angeles|ref=none}}\n* {{citation |surname=Wang |given=Zhenping |title=Tang China in Multi-Polar Asia: A History of Diplomacy and War |year=2013 |isbn=978-0-8248-3644-3 |ref=none}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category multi|Tang Dynasty|Art of the Tang dynasty}}\n{{NIE Poster|T\u2019ang}}\n* [http://www.metmuseum.org/toah/hd/tang/hd_tang.htm The Tang Dynasty] at the Metropolitan Museum of Art\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110806080810/http://etext.virginia.edu/chinese/frame.htm Home of 300 Tang Poems], University of Virginia\n* [http://www.artsmia.org/art-of-asia/history/dynasty-tang.cfm Tang art with video commentary], from the Minneapolis Institute of Arts\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070813175029/http://www.xabusiness.com/china-resources/sui-tang-chinese-paintings.htm Paintings of Sui and Tang dynasties]\n* ''[[Zizhi Tongjian]]'', vols. [[:zh:s:\u8cc7\u6cbb\u901a\u9451/\u5377182|182]], [[:zh:s:\u8cc7\u6cbb\u901a\u9451/\u5377183|183]], [[:zh:s:\u8cc7\u6cbb\u901a\u9451/\u5377184|184]], [[:zh:s:\u8cc7\u6cbb\u901a\u9451/\u5377185|185]], [[:zh:s:\u8cc7\u6cbb\u901a\u9451/\u5377186|186]], [[:zh:s:\u8cc7\u6cbb\u901a\u9451/\u5377187|187]]